assessment_comment: Another wash out in the fall of 2021. This is an example of an extremely violent channel forming disturbance event. Mega bridge washout downstream with significant amount of erosion of historic coal creek township. Ridge on tributary downstream has also been washed out and that's not hesitation of some of this debris could have been part of the reason of the extreme damage downstream. 17:15:44

Channel is dry approx. 120m upstream of culvert. Small trickle of water entering culvert from under substrate. Water is flowing under culvert directly into pool at outlet. No water flowing through culvert at this time. 15-20 WCT present in pool. 11:11:24
